        "start": "0:02:20.28",
        "end": "0:02:23"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 35,
    "text": "But then everyone on it was like, whose country is it?",
    "confidence": 0.9048,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:23",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:26.28",
        "start": "0:02:23",
        "end": "0:02:26.28"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 36,
    "text": "You see, there were the Greeks, or like the OGS, and there were the Turks, who moved in with the more recent empire.",
    "confidence": 0.891,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:26.48",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:31",
        "start": "0:02:26.48",
        "end": "0:02:31"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 37,
    "text": "Even with hundreds of years of shared history, Greek and Turkish Cypriots lived mostly separate from each other, with distinct towns, schools, and churches.",
    "confidence": 0.9627,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:31.32",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:38.28",
        "start": "0:02:31.32",
        "end": "0:02:38.28"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 38,
    "text": "Basically, there was little homogenization.",
    "confidence": 0.8863,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:38.48",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:40.4",
        "start": "0:02:38.48",
        "end": "0:02:40.4"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 39,
    "text": "The Turks were really not keen on becoming part of Greece, while the Greeks were really keen on becoming part of Greece.",
    "confidence": 0.9219,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:41.12",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:45.52",
        "start": "0:02:41.12",
        "end": "0:02:45.52"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 40,
    "text": "And this dichotomy escalated and snowballed into outright violence, this one off and on for year after year as the one central government barely functioned.",
    "confidence": 0.8905,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:45.52",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:53.12",
        "start": "0:02:45.52",
        "end": "0:02:53.12"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 41,
    "text": "And then some people who really wanted union with Greece did a coup in response.",
    "confidence": 0.9335,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:53.12",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:02:57",
        "start": "0:02:53.12",
        "end": "0:02:57"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 42,
    "text": "Turkey, the country invaded from the north under the justification of protecting the constitutional rights of Turkish Cypriots and basically took control of a portion of the islands.",
    "confidence": 0.8976,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:02:57.12",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:04.32",
        "start": "0:02:57.12",
        "end": "0:03:04.32"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 43,
    "text": "After a bunch of spicy diplomacy, they made that DMZ and sort of the two populations into the two sides like an eighth grade dance against one wall, the Republic of Cyprus against the other N Cyprus.",
    "confidence": 0.9349,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
