        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:20.28",
        "start": "0:03:14.96",
        "end": "0:03:20.28"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 45,
    "text": "But instead of being divided by a vast oddity, Gymnatorium Cyprus has a DMZ, and people on the northern side of it really do say they're a completely different country from the South.",
    "confidence": 0.8768,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:20.72",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:28.48",
        "start": "0:03:20.72",
        "end": "0:03:28.48"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 46,
    "text": "The only guy who agrees with them is Big Daddy Turkey, meaning this is a de facto state that entirely acts like a country but isn't recognized by anyone except Turkey.",
    "confidence": 0.9284,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:28.72",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:36.36",
        "start": "0:03:28.72",
        "end": "0:03:36.36"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": 47,
    "text": "Now we're back to the airport, because literally no one but Turkey thinks Northern Cyprus is its own country.",
    "confidence": 0.879,
    "speakerId": 1,
    "language": "en-US",
    "instances": [
      {
        "adjustedStart": "0:03:37",
        "adjustedEnd": "0:03:41.48",
        "start": "0:03:37",
        "end": "0:03:41.48"
      }
    ]
  },
